---
description: Used for frontend and backend development in Typescript
globs: *.ts, *.tsx
---
- Braces: Allman style (opening brace on new line).
- Indentation: 4 spaces.
- Strings: Double quotes.
- Types: Use type definitions, avoid interfaces.
- Architecture: Functional programming over classes.
- Functions: Always declare return types.
- Syntax: Use function declarations.
- Iteration: Use "for" loops instead of forEach().
- Nullability: Prefer undefined over null.
- Type Safety: No "any", use explicit types.
- Imports: keep them on one line.
- Documentation: JSDoc for function signatures. Keep it clear and concise. Separate function description with an empty line.
- Add packages in package.json + npm update, not via npm install.
